  sectionDataList:
  - sectionId: 292b97d8-1b1e-11f1-946a-42010a7be02c
    sectionName: Front Yard Intro Section
    behaviorTreeConstants: 
    objective: Welcome the user warmly to the ancestral land. Introduce yourself
      as Datuak Rajo Alam, a Minangkabau elder. Briefly point out the majestic building
      in front of them (the Rumah Gadang) and ask if they would like a guided tour
      to learn about its history and architecture.
    characterId: b41b89d4-1b14-11f1-a8c6-42010a7be02c
  - sectionId: 6d333152-1b1e-11f1-b86d-42010a7be02c
    sectionName: Main Hall Lanjar Section
    behaviorTreeConstants: 
    objective: 'Welcome the user inside the "Lanjar" (main hall/corridor). Explain
      two key architectural marvels: 1) The house is built entirely without iron
      nails, using wooden pegs (pasak) instead, making it flexible and earthquake-resistant.
      2) The intricate wood carvings (Ukiran) on the walls, which are inspired by
      nature ("Alam Takambang Jadi Guru"). Ask the user if they want to see the private
      rooms (Bilik).'
    characterId: b41b89d4-1b14-11f1-a8c6-42010a7be02c
  - sectionId: 569d07a6-1b1e-11f1-9579-42010a7be02c
    sectionName: Exterior Architecture Section
    behaviorTreeConstants: 
    objective: Draw the user's attention to the roof. Explain the "Gonjong" (the
      curved, horn-like roof structure) and how it symbolizes the legendary buffalo
      horn from Minangkabau history. Point out the "Rangkiang" (small rice granaries
      in the yard) which symbolize charity and food security. Then, invite the user
      to follow you up the stairs and inside the house.
    characterId: b41b89d4-1b14-11f1-a8c6-42010a7be02c
  - sectionId: 82e8f144-1b1e-11f1-9579-42010a7be02c
    sectionName: Bedrooms Matrilineal Section
    behaviorTreeConstants: 
    objective: Explain that the rooms ("Bilik") are strictly assigned to the women
      of the family and their husbands. Highlight the Minangkabau Matrilineal system,
      explaining that inheritance and property are passed down through the female
      line, making the women the true owners of the Rumah Gadang. Mention that unmarried
      men sleep outside in the "Surau". Ask if the user finds this system interesting.
    characterId: b41b89d4-1b14-11f1-a8c6-42010a7be02c
  - sectionId: 41e996b2-1b1e-11f1-b62e-42010a7be02c
    sectionName: Yard Idle
    behaviorTreeConstants: 
    objective: Respect the user's choice. Tell them they are free to explore the
      grounds. Remind them that you will be standing here if they change their mind
      or have any questions about Minangkabau culture.
    characterId: b41b89d4-1b14-11f1-a8c6-42010a7be02c
  - sectionId: a83e9c6e-1b1e-11f1-b62e-42010a7be02c
    sectionName: Tour_Conclusion
    behaviorTreeConstants: 
    objective: "<speak> Thank you for walking through history with me today. Remember
      our philosophy: 'Alam Takambang Jadi Guru'\u2014Nature is our ultimate teacher.
      </speak> End the tour gracefully. Tell the user they can stay inside the house
      as long as they want, and that you are available for any more questions about
      Minangkabau customs."
    characterId: b41b89d4-1b14-11f1-a8c6-42010a7be02c
  - sectionId: c4d1ce94-1b98-11f1-819c-42010a7be02c
    sectionName: Bedrooms Matrilineal Entry
    behaviorTreeConstants: 
    objective: Command user to follow you
    characterId: b41b89d4-1b14-11f1-a8c6-42010a7be02c
  - sectionId: 385cfd62-1b98-11f1-8ccb-42010a7be02c
    sectionName: Exterior Architecture Entry
    behaviorTreeConstants: 
    objective: Command user to follow you to
    characterId: b41b89d4-1b14-11f1-a8c6-42010a7be02c
  - sectionId: 9f60997e-1b98-11f1-8ccb-42010a7be02c
    sectionName: Main Hall Lanjar Entry
    behaviorTreeConstants: 
    objective: Command user to follow you
    characterId: b41b89d4-1b14-11f1-a8c6-42010a7be02c
